1Ô∏è‚É£ Go to your project folder
    cd path/to/your/project

2Ô∏è‚É£ Initialize Git (this creates .git)
    git init

3Ô∏è‚É£ Check file status (MOST IMPORTANT habit)
    git status

4Ô∏è‚É£ Add files to staging area
    git add .
    git add filename

5Ô∏è‚É£ Commit (this is NOT optional)
    git commit -m "Initial commit"

6Ô∏è‚É£ Rename branch to main (do this once)
    git branch -M main

7Ô∏è‚É£ Add remote repository (critical step)
    git remote add origin https://github.com/USERNAME/REPO_NAME.git
      Check it: git remote -v

8Ô∏è‚É£ Push to remote (GitHub)
    git push -u origin main         (so next time just "git push")

üîÅ Daily workflow after this:
    git status
    git add .
    git commit -m "Meaningful message"
    git push

    

üéÄ if git refusing to merge unrelated histories 
üëç then use: 
    Step 1: Abort any half state (clean slate)
        git merge --abort
    
	Step 2: Pull with permission to merge histories
        git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories